reviewText: Julia Roberts has been in a league of her of her own for a vey long time and I thought I owned all of her movies. This was not only a great DVD collection; it's simply has some of the movies that I missed. Its a very cute collection of a superstar woman that continues to be just herself and a hell of an actress as well. I think this collecion finishes out my current collection and will await for the newest releases to come forth so I don't miss a beat!
Have seen three of the four and love the ones I have seen including of course Julia Roberts.  Another bang for your buck deal.

Favorite movie set but could not get subtitles to work!

My husband and I had seen "Notting Hill" in the theatres and maybe once on TV before I purchased this 4-in-one.  We like the movie, but think it's a bit unrealistic as a story.  However, it's entertaining.  Hugh Grant is Hugh Grant, with his special forehead-emphasized tousled hair and his eye expressions.  That's worth a star right there.  "Charlie Wilson's War" is a really good movie, well produced and fast paced.  We should have used "closed captions" right off the bat because Philip Seymour Hoffman's dialogue is so rapid-fire, we older folks with aging ears needed a "slow-up button."  "Duplicity" was fair and kind of nutty.  Julia Roberts is versatile and her acting in that role is believable, even when she is mean.  We haven't watched "Larry Crowne" yet, because I saw it on TV and got a little bored.  Maybe we'll watch it on the 4-in-1 soon.
A generally pleasant collection; Charlie Wilson's War being edgier (thanks to Phillip Seymour Hoffman) than the others.
Two good movies and two suspects.
Good deal if you like Julia Roberts.
